
[1]hilarity

   HILAR'ITY, n. [L. hilaritas; Gr. joyful, merry.]

   Mirth; merriment; gayety. Hilarity differs from joy; the latter,
   excited by good news or prosperity, is an affection of the mind; the
   former, by social pleasure, drinking, &c., which rouse the animal
   spirits.
